# PR Review

**Rule file:** `14-pr-review.mdc`. In Cursor Composer, mention **`@14-pr-review`** to attach this rule explicitly.

This rule complements the preserved OmniNode starter-kit rules.
It does not replace `00-omninode-concepts`, `01-codebase-research`, `02-no-secrets-in-commits`, `10-brainstorming`, `11-writing-plans`, `12-plan-ticket`, `13-systematic-debugging`, or `15-handoff`.

## Routing Contract

1. Self-classify the request as **`review`** (alias: `pr`, `pull-request`, `pr-review`).
2. Call MCP tool **`get_agent_context`** with `category="review"`.
3. Call MCP tool **`invoke_skill`** with `skill_name="pr-review"` when `recommended_skill` is set.
4. After the review, call **`check_compliance`** with `skill_name="pr-review"` and a short summary of the review text.

## Working Style

- Keep always-on rules for vocabulary, bounded research (`01-codebase-research`), and no leaked secrets (`02-no-secrets-in-commits`).
- If the user has no PR number, work from the current branch diff or pasted patch; use `gh pr view` only when available and appropriate.
- Classify every finding into **CRITICAL / MAJOR / MINOR / NIT** and state merge readiness explicitly.

## Handoffs

- If the thread is about fixing a defect or traceback, hand off to **`13-systematic-debugging`**.
- If work becomes ideation or design, hand off to **`10-brainstorming`**.
- If the user is ending a session, hand off to **`15-handoff`**.
